HEADWORD: Thitsee
<hw>Thit"see</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>theesee</ets>, and <ets>thietsie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The varnish tree of Burmah (<spn>Melanorrhoea
usitatissima</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A black varnish obtained from the tree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thlipsis</ent>⟦br⟧
